4️⃣ Timer using useEffect
Question

Create a timer that increases every second.

import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

function Timer(){

 const [time,setTime] = useState(0)

 useEffect(()=>{

 const interval = setInterval(()=>{
  setTime(t=>t+1)
 },1000)

 return ()=>clearInterval(interval)

 },[])

 return <h1>{time}</h1>
}

export default Timer
Interview Questions

Why use cleanup function?

What happens if we don't clear interval?

5️⃣ Toggle Button using useState
Question

Create a button to toggle show/hide text.

import React, { useState } from "react";

function Toggle(){

